              • alex.mojaki.boxes.collections.ListBox<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the list elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Box<List<E>>, PowerBox<List<E>>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>

    public class ListBox<E>
extends CollectionBox<List<E>,E>
implements List<E>
    A list that can watch for changes. This is both a List and a PowerBox<List> and should be declared as this type so that it can use the abilities of both. It is far preferable to creating a PowerBox in a more usual way, e.g. a CommonBox<List>, as you can now attach ChangeObservers that know when the list is mutated, which also implies you can create Views around it.
    See Also:
    WrapperBox
